This file contains information about the scripts related to smallscript:

==broadening.py==
This script calculates the broadenend spectrum using a given line-spectrum. There are several options availible like specifying a grid or just its range, the broadening paraemeter and so on. 
As functions, gaussian and lorentzian shapes are available

==ConEn.py==
This script can be used to extract the binding energies during g09-optimisation. 

==Duschinsky_unrestricted.py and Btree.py==
The functions and classes belong to a method to calculate the FC factors by taking into account the Duschinsky rotation. 
Since this leads to memory blow-ups for those molecules considered here, THE FUNCTIONS ARE NOT TESTED.
